.TH "igc_add_mac_filter" 9 "igc_add_mac_filter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
igc_add_mac_filter \- Add MAC address filter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" igc_add_mac_filter
.BI "(struct igc_adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "enum igc_mac_filter_type type "  ","
.BI "const u8 *addr "  ","
.BI "int queue "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
Pointer to adapter where the filter should be added
.IP "type" 12
MAC address filter type (source or destination)
.IP "addr" 12
MAC address
.IP "queue" 12
If non-negative, queue assignment feature is enabled and frames
matching the filter are enqueued onto 'queue'. Otherwise, queue
assignment is disabled.
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success, negative errno code otherwise.
